Explanation of properties file::-
---------------------------------
1️.spring.kafka.bootstrap-servers=localhost:9092
This tells your Spring Boot app where Kafka is running.
localhost → Kafka broker machine
9092 → default Kafka port
=>“This property is used to connect the application to the Kafka broker cluster.”

2️.spring.kafka.consumer.group-id=order-group
This defines the consumer group name.
All consumers with the same group-id
Share the load of partitions
Each message is processed once per group
=>“Consumer group ensures scalability and fault tolerance. If one instance goes down, another takes over.”

3️.spring.kafka.consumer.auto-offset-reset=earliest
What to do if no offset exists for this consumer group.
earliest	Start from beginning
latest	Start from new messages
🧠 Why earliest?
Useful during development
Ensures no message is missed
=>“If the consumer has no committed offset, it starts reading from the beginning of the topic.”

4.spring.kafka.consumer.value-deserializer=org.springframework.kafka.support.serializer.JsonDeserializer
Kafka messages are received as JSON and converted into Java objects.

5.spring.kafka.consumer.properties.spring.json.trusted.packages=*
Allows Kafka to deserialize classes from any package.
=>Production best practice: spring.json.trusted.packages=com.example.order.model

6.spring.kafka.producer.value-serializer=org.springframework.kafka.support.serializer.JsonSerializer
Converts Java objects → JSON before sending to Kafka.

